{
  "article_id": "Taylor1860_12(11)",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "[...]"
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Concerning the Islands of "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Miguel",
        "entity_key": "i_sm",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " and "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Rosa",
        "entity_key": "i_sr",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", not a native of these Islands is now to be found in or near "
      },
      {
        "text": "this Mission",
        "entity_key": "mi_santabarbaramission",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", nor one who could give any information of them."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Among the Indians of Santa Barbara exist some traditions that do not extend to more than one century, which is not to be surprised at on account of being in their uncivilized state of gentilism before, and consequently, no care taken to give them to posterity. Those received from their fathers, and grandfathers, they know; but of their great-grandfathers and ancestors, then can scarcely know anything. About the passing of ships, they know nothing more than from time to time seeing one pass at a great distance."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "When "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Franciscan Missionary Fathers",
        "entity_key": "misfats",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " arrived in "
      },
      {
        "text": "California",
        "entity_key": "re_spcal",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " they found tribes of Indians scattered along "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Coast",
        "entity_key": "re_calcoast",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", from "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Diego",
        "entity_key": "ci_sd",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " to the "
      },
      {
        "text": "bay of San Francisco",
        "entity_key": "re_sfbay",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and varying in number to about two thousand, in each of the larger tribes. They enlightened them with the light of the Gospel, and founded for them "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Missions",
        "entity_key": "mi_mainlandmissions",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " to be seen at the present day. "
      },
      {
        "text": "They were of a generous, and generally docile nature, copper-colored, and highly favored by the Omnipotent Arm in strength and other corporeal qualities.",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The boats they then used were canoes cut out of trees, or made of timber joined with chords, and these tarred (with asphalte? [asphaltum]) and not capable of carrying more than four persons. Their houses were not made of stone, but of timber and reeds, in a bee-hive shape."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Along "
      },
      {
        "text": "the coast",
        "entity_key": "re_calcoast",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " and "
      },
      {
        "text": "islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " each tribe generally spoke a different language, but understood sufficient of their neighboring idioms for the purpose of commerce. With regard to grammatical construction in their language, it is superfluous to say they knew it not. The foregoing vocabulary of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Cruz",
        "entity_key": "i_scruz",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " has been taken from one of its natives. Take notice that it has to be pronounced like English, as it has been so written, and accurately, as the gutteral sound of the language would permit. "
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The Indians['] name of the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Island of Santa Cruz",
        "entity_key": "i_scruz",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " was Limooh or Limoo-eh. For the "
      },
      {
        "text": "island of Santa Rosa",
        "entity_key": "i_sr",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " the name was Hurmal, that of "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Miguel",
        "entity_key": "i_sm",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " was Two-a-can, that of "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "was Ghalashat."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "For the foregoing vocabulary and notes "
      },
      {
        "text": "the compiler",
        "entity_key": "ata",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " is indebted to the kindness of the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Rt. Rev. Teodoro Amat",
        "entity_key": "tbr",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", Catholic Bishop of the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Diocese of Monterey",
        "entity_key": "ch_diocese",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The Indian",
        "entity_key": "indian1",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who gave the information, did not know the names of elk, wolf, beaver, squirrel, hare, duck, pigeon, tufted quail, nor the term for one thousand."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "An old American resident",
        "entity_key": "american",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " informs me that the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " were pretty thickly populated in the early part of this century prior to 1816. "
      },
      {
        "text": "They had such bloody wars among themselves, for the fishing-grounds of each island, or each rancheria, that ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the priests",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "misfats",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " had them all brought over to ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the main land",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "re_mld",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " and placed in the Missions of ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "mi_santabarbaramission",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Luis Obispo",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "mi_slo",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Buenaventura",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "mi_venturamission",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Ynez",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "mi_sy",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " and ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "La Purisima",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "mi_pur",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "; but that very few, if any, are now left in those vicinities.",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " off the coast of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "co_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Diego",
        "entity_key": "co_sdcounty",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " and "
      },
      {
        "text": "Los Angeles",
        "entity_key": "co_la",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " countries [counties], are "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Miguel",
        "entity_key": "i_sm",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Cruz",
        "entity_key": "i_scruz",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Rosa",
        "entity_key": "i_sr",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "i_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Cataline",
        "entity_key": "i_scatalina",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " and "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Clemente",
        "entity_key": "i_scl",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and they are mentioned by "
      },
      {
        "text": "Cabrillo",
        "entity_key": "jca",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " in 1542, as being inhabited, and by "
      },
      {
        "text": "Viscaino",
        "entity_key": "svi",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "'s in 1602, as (some of them) being very populous. "
      },
      {
        "text": "On ",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Catalina",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_scatalina",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", Viscaino's vessels stopped several days, and were treated by ",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indians",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_Catalineno",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " with great hospitality.",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "The historian of the expedition",
        "entity_key": "carp",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " mentions the existence of a rude temple and worship of the sun by "
      },
      {
        "text": "the natives",
        "entity_key": "natam_Catalineno",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and of an immense black crow (probably the Condor), which was an object of great veneration among them, and on the shooting of which by "
      },
      {
        "text": "a Spanish soldier",
        "entity_key": "spsol",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indians",
        "entity_key": "natam_Catalineno",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " set up an awful howling of tremor and fear. This veneration of the Great Bird of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Northwest America",
        "entity_key": "re_nwamerica",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " seems to have been universal among the California Indians; a reference will be found made to this subject in "
      },
      {
        "text": "Dr. Herman",
        "entity_key": "ahe",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "'s Ornithological Notes in the tenth volume of Railroad Reports."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Great havoc was committed on these ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "island-tribes",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_NicolenoTongva",
          "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
          "natam_chumash"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " by the Indians of the main land, and ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "those from the Northwest",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_aleuts",
          "natam_kodiak"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ". We believe these ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Northwest Indians",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_aleuts",
          "natam_kodiak"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "were ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Kodiaks and others, in the employ of the Russians",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "1814huntingparty",
          "rfurcompany",
          "iba",
          "natam_aleuts",
          "natam_kodiak"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " of ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Bodega",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "ci_bodega",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " and ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Sitka",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "ci_si",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", in search of sea-otters, fur-seals, and avelones [abalones], who used to make raids on their own account. In ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Hugo Reid",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "hre",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "'s account of the Indians of ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Los Angeles county",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "co_la",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", published in the ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Los Angeles Star",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "lastar",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", in 1852, it is stated that ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the Missionaries",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "misfats",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " gathered ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the enemies",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_aleuts",
          "natam_kodiak"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " from caves on ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the islands",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " of many of ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the San Clemente Indians",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", between 1825 and 1833, and had them decently buried, and what was singular every one of the skulls were found with a double row of teeth, both on the lower and upper jaw.",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": " How true this statement is can only be ascertained by disentombing the bodies, which, it seems, were buried either at "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Gabriel",
        "entity_key": "mi_sg",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Diego",
        "entity_key": "mi_sd",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", or "
      },
      {
        "text": "Juan Capistrano",
        "entity_key": "mi_jc",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " Missions."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "In one of the raids of these ",
        "tropes": [
          11,
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Kodiak Indians",
        "tropes": [
          11,
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_kodiak",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " they are said to have killed every Indian on the ",
        "tropes": [
          11,
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "island of San Nicholas",
        "tropes": [
          11,
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " execpt ",
        "tropes": [
          11,
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "two or three women",
        "tropes": [
          11,
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "; and only a short time ago appeared an account in the California journals of ",
        "tropes": [
          11,
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "one of these females",
        "tropes": [
          11,
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " (or ",
        "tropes": [
          11,
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the last inhabitant of the island",
        "tropes": [
          11,
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ") having, with great difficulty, been taken off by the old California hunter, ",
        "tropes": [
          11,
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "George Nidever",
        "tropes": [
          11,
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and carried to ",
        "tropes": [
          11,
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "tropes": [
          11,
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " in a semi-demented state.",
        "tropes": [
          11,
          6
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "An American otter hunter",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who has been engaged among the ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara Islands",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "for the last six years, and who has visited every one of the California islands, from ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Cedros island",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_cedros",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " to ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the Farallones",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_far",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", informs me that the remains of ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indians",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_NicolenoTongva",
          "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
          "natam_chumash"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " in ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the Channel islands",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", from ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Catalina",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_scatalina",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", up, indicate a very numerous population of ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Indians",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_NicolenoTongva",
          "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
          "natam_chumash"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ". There are supposed to be no ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Island Indians",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_NicolenoTongva",
          "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
          "natam_chumash"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " left now, neither on ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the main land",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "re_mld",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", or elsewhere, certainly none at their former homes.",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
